It was a remarkable defense of the Sixth Amendment that points toward a broad decision restoring the jury trial right to some of the country’s most maligned defendants.
Under this law, a judge must sentence offenders to additional prison time—from five years to life—if they violate the terms of their release.
And why isn’t one of those consequences the jury right?”As usual, Justice Sonia Sotomayor was right at Gorsuch side defending the Sixth Amendment.
That would be an important victory for the Sixth Amendment, and an affirmation that the government cannot lock away sex offenders for life without a jury’s input.
As Scalia wrote in 2003, however, the jury trial “has never been efficient”—but “it has always been free.”